The Elven Caestopaeifs served their world well, giving many weapons painstakingly designed. However, most of the schools of such crafters hide dark secrets.Being obedient to wise gravekeeping seers, they prepare carcasses for rituals comparable with grave-robbery. The spirits of the fallen warriors occupy cold animated statues of tough eldritch material to fight against alien occupants, so the living Elves could hear songs of joy ever again. Monsoon Warhost of Beal-Tanny remember the desperate action to revive dead exile brethren from their defiled Kurghans on paradise world of Taran, so they could avenge on aliens as mighty undead gargantuans in the war.

The Smallwraith models are made using model builder by Karadryel (https://cults3d.com/en/users/Karadryel/3d-models)
The Ligma Razor model is a free model by Spear Miniatures
(https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/d-reaper-gun-only)

UPDATE:
2023 August 15th - separate legs for CQC Smallwraith models added, now the models have new Phantom Swords and Spook Bardiche objects appropriate for printing in 8mm scale.

NOTICE:
- the models are not tested yet, there’re no supported stls required for safe printing, so the prints are required for experienced hobbyists;
- model sturdiness, especially Phantom Swords variants, is questionable;
- the preview images are dated.

THANKS TO:
Mannschaft for Smallwraith models test printing and reporting for flaws found;
MKhand_Industries for supporting and suggesting ideas (https://cults3d.com/en/users/Mkhand_Industries/creations)

The Empire of Sentient Man cannot reclaim constant victories over space elves who constantly terrorize human realms. But this doesn’t mean they cannot beat the foe in local skirmishes. The local victories provided to imperials limited weapon exhibits to examine. Besides many elven hover vehicles with controversial fusion of organic and greebled shaped apparatus, defenders of man had found many weapons considered by logics of military art. Some hover tank platoons are followed by self-propelled anti-aircraft engines based on the same platform. They got different names, but the Red Militia called them Zeus. The alternate name was provided due to role similar to small multilaser flak cannons the militia operate.

This model is a turret required for building self-propelled anti-aircraft based on Tiny Space Elves - Beam Hover Tank by Lord_Chronos (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-beam-hover-tank)

UPDATE 2023.12.14:
- new pin on the turret bottom to fit Beam Hover Tank by Lord_Chronos.

NOTICE:
This model is test printed using Chitubox software, so be careful.

Aetherhawk is a space elven school of crafty Caestopaeifs, infamous for their extremes. Their master architect looked at the needs of world’s Warhost and decided to craft small scale war machines, intended to support smaller warrior squads. He succeeded in providing hover tanks for pathfinding warriors, unaware of the flaws that might bring Warhost in peril. The artisans of friendly Ymbloc world were dissatisfied by greebly looks of apparatus that is supposed to bring energy support to hover vehicles. They stated, the creations of Aetherhawk are a deviation of elven vital designs.

This model is a hull required for building alternate Tiny Space Elves - Transport Hover Tankby Lord_Chronos (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-transport-hover-tank)

- new hole on the bottom for flying stem.

This model is test printed using Chitubox software, so be careful

The Empire of Sentient Man has the diverse army taking part in permament war against the foul traitors and treacherous aliens. Mostly, the army is represented by ill-equipped militia in various ballistic armour (including coats), wielding only laser rifles. Red Militia has such a tragic fate. While being the defenders of their land, they have to reach the planets too far beyond comprehension, test the mud with their boots and treads and hope for weapons to beat unfamiliar threats.

The Red Militia models, with faces diminished and bases added, are shared for free with the permission of NotANiceGuy (https://cults3d.com/en/users/NotANiceGuy/3d-models).

The pack contains:
- command squad including lieutenant, communication officer, standard bearer and sergeant;
- line infantry in 8 different poses;
- heavy weapons teams with heavy machine gun, automatic gun, laser cannon, missile launcher;
- random loaders and mortar crew;
- plus non-Red Militia 3 commissars and 2 psykers.

UPDATE 2023.08.15:
- added separate heavy weapons;
- improved missile launcher crew, version two added;
- mortars added.

UPDATE 2023.12.14:
- Master of Discipline model added;
- All the Red Militia are downscaled to fit 8mm scale;
- All the weapons on carriages are downscaled;
- New Missile Launcher team for nostalgic feels.

Pictures with resin prints of pre-release version of 8mm Red Militia models included. The current models have sturdier bases, and the standard bearer got thicker banner pole.
